13:47.590 --> 13:51.356
WAS THIS WARDROBE CHANGE
MORE OF AN OLFACTORY ISSUE?

13:55.900 --> 13:57.299
YOU TELL ME.

13:57.300 --> 13:58.369
[ LAUGHS ]

14:00.840 --> 14:02.637
I DROPPED MY SALAD.

14:02.640 --> 14:04.938
YOU CAN'T REALLY GET VINAIGRETTE
OUT WITH A WET PAPER TOWEL.

14:04.940 --> 14:09.434
THEY'RE DOING AN ARTICLE ON ME
FOR THE NEPTUNE REGISTER.

14:09.440 --> 14:11.203
THE INTERVIEW'S
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS,

14:11.210 --> 14:13.872
BUT THEY'VE GOT A PHOTOGRAPHER
DUE HERE ANY MINUTE.

14:13.880 --> 14:16.178
AND YOU THOUGHT A PHOTO
OF YOU IN YOUR BOXERS

14:16.180 --> 14:17.784
WOULD HURT YOUR LEAD
IN THE POLLS?

14:17.790 --> 14:21.180
WITH CLEAN PANTS, IT'S A SMOOTH
CRUISE INTO VICTORY.

14:21.190 --> 14:24.921
AND WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY THAT
WILL BE FOR MARS, THE FAMILY;

14:24.930 --> 14:27.956
NEPTUNE, THE TOWN;
MILKY WAY, THE GALAXY.

14:27.960 --> 14:30.520
SUN WILL BE SHINING.
BIRDS WILL BE SINGING.

14:30.530 --> 14:32.623
THERE'LL BE DANCING
IN THE STREETS.

14:32.630 --> 14:35.531
SO SMILE PRETTY.

14:35.540 --> 14:37.030
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

14:42.210 --> 14:43.643
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THE CASTLE IS?

14:43.650 --> 14:45.948
I THINK I'VE HEARD
SOMETHING ABOUT IT.

14:45.950 --> 14:48.942
IT'S HEARST'S VERSION
OF SKULL AND BONES.

14:48.950 --> 14:51.145
THEY TAPPED ME TO JOIN.

14:51.750 --> 14:53.149
SO, THIS MORNING --

14:53.160 --> 14:54.479
THIS MORNING, I DIDN'T THINK
THAT THE CASTLE

14:54.490 --> 14:57.550
HAD ANYTHING TO DO
WITH THAT TAPE.

14:57.560 --> 14:58.879
NOW I DO.

14:59.560 --> 15:02.222
THIS GIRL CALLED ME A FEW DAYS
AGO WANTING TO HANG OUT,

15:02.230 --> 15:03.492
AND I BRUSHED HER OFF.

15:03.500 --> 15:05.161
BASICALLY,
I LIED AND TOLD HER

15:05.170 --> 15:07.593
I HAD TO GO TO A STUDY NIGHT
AT MY PROFESSOR'S HOUSE.

15:07.600 --> 15:11.001
AFTER I SAW YOU TODAY,
MY PROFESSOR GAVE ME THIS.

15:11.010 --> 15:14.002
IT'S A MESSAGE
FROM THE CASTLE.

15:14.010 --> 15:16.035
THEY KNEW
WHERE I WAS SUPPOSED TO BE.

15:16.040 --> 15:17.576
THEY BUGGED YOU?

15:17.580 --> 15:19.798
YEAH, AND IT JUST MAKES SENSE
THAT IT'S THE SAME DEVICE

15:19.810 --> 15:21.573
THEY USED
TO CATCH YOU AND PIZ.

15:21.580 --> 15:24.287
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.

15:24.290 --> 15:25.814
I'M GONNA NEED NAMES AND --

15:25.820 --> 15:28.380
I HAVEN'T MET A SINGLE PERSON --
NOT EVEN ANOTHER PLEDGE.

15:28.390 --> 15:30.620
THE PERSON WHO TAPPED ME,
HE ISN'T EVEN A MEMBER.

15:30.630 --> 15:33.224
THE WHOLE RUSH PROCESS
IS DONE IN MESSAGES.

15:33.230 --> 15:35.528
WELL, THEY GOT ONE LESS GUY
TO TORTURE IN HELL NIGHT.

15:35.530 --> 15:38.658
ANY CHANCE
YOU'D RECONSIDER THAT?

15:42.700 --> 15:44.861
I'M SORRY.
THAT'S CRAZY.

15:44.870 --> 15:47.577
THAT'S WAY TOO MUCH
TO ASK.

15:50.480 --> 15:52.072
IT'S NOT.

15:52.080 --> 15:53.570
I CAN DO IT.

15:54.980 --> 15:56.413
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO GET NAMES?

15:56.420 --> 15:58.581
I HAVE A FEELING
THERE'S NO I.D. TAGS.

16:03.790 --> 16:04.984
JUST GET THEIR FACES.

16:04.990 --> 16:07.493
YOU KNOW I CAN'T DRAW,
RIGHT?

16:07.500 --> 16:08.922
IT'S A CAMERA.

16:08.930 --> 16:12.093
SNAP A FEW SHOTS OF THE GUYS
WHEN YOU CAN.

16:12.100 --> 16:14.091
WHEN I GOT TAPPED,
I WENT TO THE HEARST LIBRARY

16:14.100 --> 16:17.638
AND LOOKED UP EVERYTHING
I COULD ON THE CASTLE.

16:17.640 --> 16:19.437
THERE WASN'T MUCH.

16:19.440 --> 16:21.408
BUT THERE WAS
THIS EXPOS.

16:24.250 --> 16:27.014
AND LOOK WHO WROTE IT.

16:31.320 --> 16:33.709
THANKS FOR MEETING ME.

16:33.720 --> 16:36.280
WHO DOESN'T LOVE A GOOD CHAT
WITH OLD FRIENDS

16:36.290 --> 16:37.848
ABOUT SECRET SOCIETIES?

16:37.860 --> 16:41.751
OUR ILLUSTRIOUS NAMESAKE WAS
A YALE SKULL AND BONES MAN.

16:41.760 --> 16:43.796
HE WANTED HEARST
TO HAVE SOMETHING SIMILAR.

16:43.800 --> 16:47.167
SO HE STARTED THE CASTLE AT
STANFORD, WHERE HIS SON WENT,

16:47.170 --> 16:49.229
AND AT HEARST,
THE SCHOOL HE FOUNDED.

16:49.240 --> 16:50.764
SO, WHAT DO THEY DO?

16:50.770 --> 16:53.102
THAT'S THE BILLION-DOLLAR
QUESTION.

16:53.110 --> 16:55.135
BEING TAPPED FOR THE CASTLE,
THEY SAY,

16:55.140 --> 16:57.540
IS A TICKET TO WEALTH,
POWER, AND PRIVILEGE.

16:57.550 --> 16:59.745
THEY'RE TREATED
LIKE ROCK STARS.

16:59.750 --> 17:01.308
SO WHO GETS TAPPED?

17:01.320 --> 17:02.878
NOTABLE FRESHMAN MALES.

17:02.880 --> 17:04.643
FUTURE POLITICIANS
AND LAWYERS.

17:04.650 --> 17:07.687
ENGINEERS, JOURNALISTS,
ATHLETES.

17:07.690 --> 17:10.750
WEALTHY MEN MAKING
OTHER LIKE-MINDED MEN WEALTHY.

17:10.760 --> 17:14.252
AND HOW DO THE LADIES
FEEL ABOUT THAT?

17:14.260 --> 17:15.659
WE'RE NOT HAPPY.

17:15.660 --> 17:17.696
A GROUP TRIED TO SUE
FOR ADMISSION LAST YEAR,

17:17.700 --> 17:20.339
BUT THEY COULDN'T FIGURE OUT
EXACTLY WHO TO SUE.

17:20.340 --> 17:23.138
NO ONE KNOWS
WHO THE MEMBERS ARE.

17:42.420 --> 17:45.253
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

17:53.740 --> 17:56.789
[ Synthesized voice ]
FIRST CORRIDOR ON YOUR LEFT.

18:02.810 --> 18:04.505
KEEP GOING.

18:07.620 --> 18:10.839
GO INTO UNIT 499.

18:23.030 --> 18:25.863
THREE, STRIP TO YOUR UNDERWEAR.

18:25.870 --> 18:28.964
TH ROW YOUR CLOTHES
OUTSIDE THE DOOR, SHUT THE DOOR,

18:28.970 --> 18:32.098
THEN PUT ON THE COLLAR
AND SIT IN THE CHAIR.

18:47.090 --> 18:49.308
[ MAN SCREAMS ]

18:50.090 --> 18:51.921
[ Synthesized voice ]
THREE, WHAT YOU DO NOW

18:51.930 --> 18:54.421
WILL DECIDE THE COURSE
OF YOUR ENTIRE FUTURE.

18:54.430 --> 18:57.524
DO EVERYTHING WE ASK, AND
THE WORLD WILL BE AT YOUR FEET.

18:57.530 --> 19:00.192
WE'RE GOING TO TALK ABOUT
THE SINS OF YOUR PAST.

19:00.200 --> 19:02.134
WE HAVE NO SECRETS
IN THE CASTLE.

19:02.140 --> 19:03.664
IF YOU LIE TO US,

19:03.670 --> 19:05.865
ONE OF YOUR PLEDGE BROTHERS
WILL PAY THE PRICE.

19:05.870 --> 19:06.905
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

19:06.910 --> 19:08.138
I UNDERSTAND.

19:08.140 --> 19:09.676
TELL US
ABOUT RASHARD RUCKER.

19:09.680 --> 19:11.739
WHAT HAPPENED
THE NIGHT IN CHICAGO

19:11.750 --> 19:14.446
WHEN YOU RAN OVER
THE HOMELESS MAN?

19:24.290 --> 19:28.954
SO YOUR FATHER COMMITTED
A CRIME FOR YOU.

19:28.960 --> 19:30.689
YEAH.

19:30.700 --> 19:33.396
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]
AAH!

19:34.440 --> 19:37.136
WHAT?
I ANSWERED.

19:37.140 --> 19:39.608
YES.
BUT SOMEONE ELSE LIED.

19:39.610 --> 19:42.829
WE ALL MUST PAY
FOR OUR BROTHERS' SINS.

19:42.840 --> 19:45.104
FINAL QUESTION --

19:45.110 --> 19:48.739
WHAT ITEM WERE YOU CARRYING
IN YOUR POCKET TONIGHT?

19:49.880 --> 19:51.245
JUST A PEN.

19:51.250 --> 19:53.411
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES,
MAN SCREAMS ]

19:53.420 --> 19:56.583
YOU WANT TO TRY
ANSWERING THAT AGAIN?

20:07.340 --> 20:10.605
[ CAR DOOR OPENS,
FOOTSTEPS ]

20:14.210 --> 20:15.438
IF YOU EVER NEED A KIDNEY,

20:15.440 --> 20:17.374
I'VE GOT ONE
WITH YOUR NAME ON IT,

20:17.380 --> 20:19.803
NO QUESTIONS ASKED.

20:22.780 --> 20:25.248
THEY KNEW ABOUT
THE CAMERA?

20:25.250 --> 20:27.218
I SAID IT WAS A PEN.

20:27.220 --> 20:29.518
THEN I HEARD
THIS SCREAM.

20:29.520 --> 20:31.385
I WOULDN'T TALK ANYMORE.

20:31.390 --> 20:33.995
THAT'S WHEN VOICE ON THE BOX
TOLD ME TO GET OUT.

20:34.000 --> 20:36.628
I'M SO SORRY.

20:38.470 --> 20:41.894
I THINK I KNOW WHO
ONE OF THE OTHER PLEDGES IS.

20:41.900 --> 20:44.266
THE VOICE ON THE BOX KEPT
CALLING ME "THREE."

20:44.270 --> 20:46.807
THREE --
MY BASKETBALL NUMBER.

20:46.810 --> 20:50.871
BUT HE SLIPPED UP ONE TIME,
AND HE CALLED ME "2,400."

20:50.880 --> 20:53.371
2,400.

20:53.380 --> 20:54.642
MEANING?

20:54.650 --> 20:56.447
THE FIRST COUPLE WEEKS
OF SCHOOL,

20:56.450 --> 20:58.145
THERE WAS A STORY
IN THE FREE PRESS

20:58.150 --> 21:01.085
ABOUT THAT FRESHMAN WHO MADE
A PERFECT SCORE ON THE S.A.T.

21:01.090 --> 21:02.717
2,400.
YEAH.

21:02.720 --> 21:05.689
THEY RAN A PICTURE OF HIM
WITH THE STORY.

21:05.690 --> 21:08.750
HE LOOKED KIND OF LIKE
JOSH GROBAN.

21:26.980 --> 21:27.844
IS THAT HIM?

21:27.850 --> 21:29.909
THAT'S THE GUY.

21:32.190 --> 21:33.612
I'LL FIND HIM.

21:33.620 --> 21:37.283
I'LL FOLLOW HIM, AND HE WILL
LEAD ME TO THE CASTLE.

21:47.440 --> 21:48.896
FRIEND OF YOURS?

21:48.900 --> 21:50.265
APPARENTLY NOT.

21:50.270 --> 21:53.808
Man: OH, ENOUGH OF THE FOREPLAY.
GET TO THE GOOD STUFF.

21:53.810 --> 21:57.302
HEY, WAIT.
DO I KNOW YOU?

21:57.310 --> 21:58.402
YOU LOOK SO FAMILIAR.

21:58.410 --> 21:59.968
COME ON, MAN.

21:59.980 --> 22:02.471
WHAT? I JUST THINK
I'VE SEEN HER SOMEWHERE BEFORE.

22:02.480 --> 22:04.038
DON'T BE A JERK.

22:04.050 --> 22:07.019
OW.
YOU GOT ME.

22:07.890 --> 22:09.187
IT'S A NICE DAY.

22:09.190 --> 22:11.750
LET'S GO EAT OUTSIDE.

22:11.760 --> 22:13.455
VERONICA?

22:13.460 --> 22:14.950
COME ON.

22:18.870 --> 22:21.430
LOOKS EVEN MORE FAMILIAR
FROM BEHIND.

22:21.440 --> 22:22.998
I PROMISE YOU,

22:23.000 --> 22:25.230
KARMA'S GOING TO TAKE CARE
OF THAT GUY FOR YOU.

22:25.240 --> 22:26.559
I KNOW.

22:26.570 --> 22:28.936
I'M GONNA RUN HIM
OVER WITH MY "KARMA."

22:30.550 --> 22:32.745
DUDE, I SAW
THAT PIZNARSKI GUY TODAY.

22:32.750 --> 22:35.810
THAT'S ONE MESSED-UP POLACK,
MY BROTHER.

22:36.420 --> 22:39.014
POUND AND EXPLODE, DUDE.
IT'S STILL A THING.

22:40.690 --> 22:42.555
[ IMITATES EXPLOSION ]

22:42.560 --> 22:44.926
I GUESS HE DIDN'T MAKE
THE VIDEO.

22:44.930 --> 22:46.682
WHOOPS. YOUR BAD.

22:46.690 --> 22:48.419
STILL,
IT WAS A ROYAL BEATDOWN.

22:48.430 --> 22:50.660
SOMETIMES A RANDOM ASS-KICKING'S
A GOOD THING.

22:50.670 --> 22:52.467
KEEPS EVERYONE ELSE
IN LINE.

23:04.950 --> 23:08.613
OH, 2,400, HOW QUICKLY
YOU'RE MOVING UP IN THE WORLD.

23:08.620 --> 23:10.110
NOT A BAD DEAL --

23:10.120 --> 23:12.247
DRIVE INTO A PARKING LOT
IN YOUR CRAP CAR,

23:12.250 --> 23:14.957
LEAVE IN A STRETCH LIMO, AND BE
CHAUFFEURED TO A MANSION.

23:14.960 --> 23:18.088
SO THE FRONT WINDOW'S
ALL CURTAINED.

23:18.090 --> 23:21.491
HOW BEST TO GET A VIEW
OF THE BACK?

23:39.580 --> 23:41.878
I NEED FACES.

23:57.870 --> 24:00.168
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

24:28.300 --> 24:30.291
GORY? YOU HAVE THAT DISK WITH
YOU?

24:30.300 --> 24:31.267
OF COURSE.

24:31.270 --> 24:33.795
LET ME SHOW YOU MY OFFICE.

24:33.800 --> 24:35.563
I'LL TAKE THAT OFF YOUR HANDS.

24:35.570 --> 24:36.969
THAT'D BE GREAT.

24:36.970 --> 24:39.734
I FEEL LIKE GOLLUM CARRYING THIS
THING AROUND.

24:39.740 --> 24:42.834
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.

24:44.710 --> 24:48.168
I LIKE THE LOOK
OF THE PLEDGES.

24:48.180 --> 24:49.317
YOU DID WELL, GORYA.

24:49.320 --> 24:50.742
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE

24:50.750 --> 24:52.547
SOME OF THE CONFESSIONS
WE GOT THIS YEAR.

24:52.550 --> 24:54.780
WELL, THEY GET WORSE.
EVERY YEAR.

24:54.790 --> 24:58.282
I NOTICED
THAT WE'RE DOWN A PLEDGE.

24:58.290 --> 24:59.484
I WASHED HIM.

24:59.490 --> 25:01.458
CAUGHT HIM SNEAKING IN
A CAMERA.

25:01.460 --> 25:03.496
CHECK IT OUT.
THERE'S THE LENS.

25:03.500 --> 25:06.560
CLICK IT --
IT TAKES A PICTURE.

25:06.570 --> 25:08.538
NEW AGE, ISN'T IT?

25:08.540 --> 25:11.907
IT LOOKS LIKE
WE'RE DONE HERE.

25:18.180 --> 25:19.374
THIS YOUR ONLY COPY?

25:19.380 --> 25:21.848
OF COURSE.

25:22.820 --> 25:24.287
[ DISC SHREDS ]

25:24.290 --> 25:25.814
[ DOG BARKS ]

25:30.990 --> 25:34.153
I WASN'T BUILT
TO LIVE IN THE SUBURBS.

25:39.500 --> 25:42.037
LET'S GO BACK
TO THE INDUCTION.

26:07.230 --> 26:09.118
NOTHING ELSE WAS TAKEN?

26:09.130 --> 26:10.529
JUST THE HARD DRIVE?

26:10.530 --> 26:13.636
WHICH HAPPENS TO BE THE MOST
VALUABLE ITEM IN THE HOUSE.

26:13.640 --> 26:14.868
WHAT WAS ON IT?

26:14.870 --> 26:16.633
IT'S FIVE YEARS
OF PROGRAMMING

26:16.640 --> 26:18.961
THAT WILL REVOLUTIONIZE
THE INDUSTRY.

26:18.970 --> 26:21.131
IT'S ALWAYS SOMETHING,
HUH?

26:21.740 --> 26:24.800
I'M SURPRISED YOU DON'T HAVE
A MASSIVE SECURITY SYSTEM, JAKE.

26:24.810 --> 26:26.448
IT'S COMING.

26:26.450 --> 26:28.816
KEITH.

26:29.650 --> 26:32.414
WELL, WE'VE ONLY BEEN HERE
FOR A MONTH.

26:32.420 --> 26:33.751
COULD HAVE BEEN
HOUSEHOLD STAFF.

26:33.760 --> 26:35.057
NO FORCED ENTRY.

26:35.060 --> 26:36.118
YOU MIND?

27:01.820 --> 27:03.742
THIS COULD BE
THE ENTRY POINT.

27:03.750 --> 27:06.048
LOOKING AT
A TINY THIEF.

27:08.660 --> 27:10.685
MR. HARVEY,
SHERIFF KEITH MARS.

27:10.690 --> 27:13.921
I'M INVESTIGATING A BREAK-IN
AT THE KANES' HOUSE NEXT DOOR.

27:13.930 --> 27:15.352
I HAPPENED TO NOTICE

27:15.360 --> 27:17.191
YOU HAD CAMERAS MOUNTED
IN YOUR BACKYARD.

27:17.200 --> 27:18.861
COME IN.

27:22.400 --> 27:24.903
THE SECURITY CAMERAS
ARE ALL HOOKED UP TO A DVR.

27:24.910 --> 27:27.105
WE'RE LOOKING AT THE BACKYARD
VIEW IN REAL TIME.

27:27.110 --> 27:30.978
BUT IF YOU HIT REWIND, YOU CAN
GO BACK UP TO THREE DAYS.

27:38.090 --> 27:40.012
THERE.
THAT WAS SOMETHING.

27:47.930 --> 27:49.898
IS THAT A GIRL?

27:54.670 --> 27:58.299
MR. HARVEY, YOU MIND
IF I TAKE THE DVR FOR EVIDENCE?

28:01.280 --> 28:02.907
EXCUSE ME.

28:06.280 --> 28:08.248
DEPUTY GILLS.

28:08.250 --> 28:09.444
IN THE FLESH.

28:09.450 --> 28:10.815
CHECK OUT THE NEW DIGS, KEITH.

28:10.820 --> 28:13.584
THIS IS WHAT I DO
SINCE YOU FIRED ME.

28:14.560 --> 28:16.755
THERE WAS A BREAK-IN
AT THE KANES' LAST NIGHT.

28:16.760 --> 28:18.284
I NEED TO SEE A LIST
OF THE PLATES

28:18.290 --> 28:20.929
OF ANY STRANGE CARS
THAT CAME IN HERE.

28:21.830 --> 28:24.219
SURE THING.
LET ME CHECK.

28:24.230 --> 28:26.323
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?
NOTHIN'.

28:26.330 --> 28:29.128
QUIET NIGHT HERE
AT PEMBERTON ESTATES.

28:29.140 --> 28:31.233
GOOD LUCK ON THE CASE,
THOUGH.

28:31.240 --> 28:34.835
HEY, BEST OF LUCK
IN THE ELECTION.

28:35.910 --> 28:38.845
LET ME EXPLAIN SOMETHING,
VERONICA.

28:38.850 --> 28:41.910
I OWN THE MOST POWERFUL
PERSONAL COMPUTER ON CAMPUS.

28:41.920 --> 28:43.785
THERE IS
NO PERSONAL COMPUTER FASTER

28:43.790 --> 28:45.143
OR BETTER THAN MINE
AT HEARST.

28:45.150 --> 28:47.118
AND USING THIS
INCREDIBLE COMPUTER OF MINE,

28:47.120 --> 28:50.351
IT WILL TAKE 20 YEARS
TO CRACK JAKE KANE'S PASSWORD

28:50.360 --> 28:51.452
ON THIS HARD DRIVE.

28:51.460 --> 28:53.325
SO HOW DO WE DO IT?

28:53.330 --> 28:54.888
YOU'RE LIKE KIRK
IN "WRATH OF KHAN."

28:54.900 --> 28:56.652
YOU REFUSE TO BELIEVE
IN THE NO-WIN SCENARIO.

28:56.660 --> 28:59.026
YOU'RE LIKE ONE OF THE NERDS
FROM "REVENGE OF THE NERDS"

28:59.030 --> 29:01.567
WITH YOUR
"STAR TREK" REFERENCES.

29:02.800 --> 29:06.759
THERE IS A COMPUTER ON CAMPUS
THAT MIGHT BE ABLE TO CRACK IT.

29:42.140 --> 29:43.402
HELLO.

29:43.410 --> 29:47.039
I NEED TO ASK YOU
ABOUT A LICENSE-PLATE NUMBER.

29:48.850 --> 29:50.078
[ BEEP ]

29:55.320 --> 29:57.686
HELLO, LOVER.

29:57.690 --> 30:01.319
GUESS THAT'S
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

30:01.330 --> 30:03.890
THAN KS.

30:06.730 --> 30:08.129
HERE WE GO.

30:11.510 --> 30:12.932
MR. HARVEY.

30:14.210 --> 30:17.179
MIND IF I TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THE SHERIFF'S VISIT?

30:32.090 --> 30:34.797
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT THE
BREAK-IN AT THE KANE MANSION?

30:34.800 --> 30:36.495
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY ROOM?

30:36.500 --> 30:37.751
DID YOU STEAL FIVE YEARS

30:37.760 --> 30:39.819
OF KANE SOFTWARE
PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT?

30:39.830 --> 30:41.969
NO.
THAT'S A CRAZY QUESTION.

30:41.970 --> 30:43.392
DID YOU TEAR APART MY ROOM?!

30:43.400 --> 30:46.335
YES. AND I FOUND THIS.
NOTICE THE RIP?

30:46.340 --> 30:49.776
I FOUND A BLUE THREAD ON A LOOSE
SCREW OF THE KANE DOGGY DOOR.

30:49.780 --> 30:53.204
TAKES SOMEONE AWFULLY SMALL TO
BREAK IN THROUGH A DOGGY DOOR.

30:53.210 --> 30:55.519
THERE ARE A LOT OF BLUE SWEATERS
IN THE WORLD.

30:55.520 --> 30:57.147
SPOKEN LIKE A PUBLIC DEFENDER,
VERONICA.

30:57.150 --> 30:58.981
IF THERE IS SOMETHING GOING ON
WITH YOU,

30:58.990 --> 31:01.311
IF YOU'RE IN TROUBLE,
NOW IS THE TIME TO TELL ME.

31:01.320 --> 31:05.120
I COULD TELL YOU, BUT YOU'D
NEVER LOOK AT ME THE SAME.

31:05.130 --> 31:07.223
I'M SPENDING THE NIGHT
AT MAC'S.

31:09.860 --> 31:13.091
VERONICA MARS?

31:13.100 --> 31:14.738
VERONICA MARS?!

31:14.740 --> 31:15.968
EASY, JAKE.

31:17.470 --> 31:19.734
AND YOU ARRANGE FOR IT
THAT I NEVER SEE THAT GIRL AGAIN

31:19.740 --> 31:21.002
IN THIS LIFETIME!

31:21.010 --> 31:23.228
YOU SURE
THAT'S OUR BEST OPTION?

31:27.880 --> 31:29.347
I WANT TO RETURN
THE SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT

31:29.350 --> 31:32.615
TO A PLACE WHERE EVERYONE,
REGARDLESS OF ZIP CODE,

31:32.620 --> 31:34.019
GETS A FAIR SHAKE.

31:34.020 --> 31:35.908
YOUR OPPONENT SAYS
HE WANTS TO BE SHERIFF

31:35.920 --> 31:37.717
BECAUSE HE ALWAYS WANTED
TO WEAR A BADGE.

31:37.720 --> 31:40.154
I'M EXCITED ABOUT THAT,
AS WELL.
[ LAUGHS ]

31:40.160 --> 31:42.196
KEITH!
IT WAS YOUR DAUGHTER, KEITH!

31:42.200 --> 31:44.862
VERONICA'S THE ONE
THAT BROKE INTO MY HOUSE

31:44.870 --> 31:46.667
AND STOLE MY HARD DRIVE!

31:46.670 --> 31:49.366
BELIEVE YOU ALREADY KNOW
THE COUNTY PROSECUTOR.

31:49.900 --> 31:51.504
AND WHAT MAKES
YOU THINK --

31:51.510 --> 31:53.262
VERONICA'S PLATES WERE
REGISTERED AT THE GUARD GATE.

31:53.270 --> 31:55.704
HER IN AND OUT TIMES
MATCH THE TIME OF THE ROBBERY.

31:55.710 --> 31:57.405
SHE'S SMALL ENOUGH.

31:57.410 --> 31:59.947
PLUS, MR. KANE'S NEIGHBOR
SAYS HIS VIDEO FOOTAGE REVEALED

31:59.950 --> 32:02.714
A BLOND GIRL
RUNNING THROUGH HIS YARD.

32:03.350 --> 32:05.545
Prosecutor: I'M GONNA NEED
THAT DVR, KEITH.

32:05.550 --> 32:07.643
I NEED IT NOW.

32:07.650 --> 32:09.652
I'LL HAPPILY TURN IT OVER

32:09.660 --> 32:12.527
AS SOON AS YOU BRING ME
A JUDGE'S ORDER.

32:13.160 --> 32:15.196
YOU KNOW WHAT
THIS LOOKS LIKE, KEITH?

32:15.200 --> 32:18.089
LIKE I DON'T KOWTOW
TO THE RICH AND POWERFUL?

32:18.100 --> 32:20.091
NO. NOT THAT.

32:20.100 --> 32:24.002
WE'LL BE BACK...
SOON.

32:29.880 --> 32:32.178
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

32:39.950 --> 32:41.486
I'LL TALK TO YOU IN AN HOUR

32:41.490 --> 32:44.584
WHEN I CAN MAKE ALL THIS
GO AWAY.

32:44.590 --> 32:47.127
COUPLE HOURS AT LEAST.

32:47.860 --> 32:49.259
WE DON'T HAVE TWO HOURS.

32:49.260 --> 32:52.423
THERE'S A CLASS SCHEDULED
IN HERE AT 9:00 AM.

32:55.170 --> 32:57.195
THIS IS VERONICA.
LEAVE ME A MESSAGE.

32:57.200 --> 32:58.406
[ BEEP ]

32:58.410 --> 32:59.604
HONEY...

32:59.610 --> 33:01.237
THINGS HAVE REALLY
HIT THE FAN DOWN HERE.

33:01.240 --> 33:04.403
I'M PRETTY DESPERATE
TO TALK TO YOU.

33:05.750 --> 33:08.071
I'M WAITING ON YOUR CALL.

34:09.110 --> 34:10.998
[ BEEP ]

34:11.010 --> 34:12.045
VERONICA!

34:12.050 --> 34:14.610
[ BEEPING ]

34:15.620 --> 34:17.372
EUREKA!

34:19.250 --> 34:21.252
THE NAMES.

34:22.860 --> 34:24.259
HUNDREDS OF THEM.

34:24.260 --> 34:27.127
THIS IS MORE THAN
ONE PLEDGE CLASS.

34:27.130 --> 34:29.997
LOOK,
THIS GUY'S CLASS OF '39?

34:30.000 --> 34:33.561
THINK WE MAY HAVE OVERSHOT.

34:33.570 --> 34:35.265
NO.

34:35.270 --> 34:38.262
THIS IS A BEAUTIFUL THING.

34:39.970 --> 34:43.337
JUDGE'S ORDERS.

34:43.340 --> 34:44.807
SEE?
THAT WASN'T HARD.

34:44.810 --> 34:47.745
LEO, YOU MIND PULLING THE DVR
FROM THE EVIDENCE ROOM

34:47.750 --> 34:50.810
AND HANDING IT OVER
TO THE COUNTY PROSECUTOR?

34:52.390 --> 34:55.757
CONFESSIONS FROM
EVERY MEMBER OF THE CASTLE

34:55.760 --> 34:57.182
SINCE ITS INCEPTION.

34:57.190 --> 34:59.158
20 YEARS
OF TRANSCRIPTIONS.

34:59.160 --> 35:03.153
AND WE HAVE
30 YEARS OF AUDIO,

35:03.160 --> 35:05.663
AND 30 YEARS OF VIDEO.

35:05.670 --> 35:07.228
WHY DO THEY DO IT?

35:07.230 --> 35:09.061
NO ONE SPILLS
THE CASTLE'S SECRETS

35:09.070 --> 35:11.265
BECAUSE THEY KNOW
WHAT THEY RISK.

35:11.270 --> 35:12.567
MOST OF THEM AREN'T GUILTY

35:12.570 --> 35:15.209
OF PUTTING THAT VIDEO OF YOU
OUT THERE.

35:17.010 --> 35:18.602
BUT THIS GUY IS.

35:18.610 --> 35:20.771
GORYA SOROKIN.

35:23.280 --> 35:24.986
SO...

35:24.990 --> 35:27.982
WE FIGURED WE'D GO UP
TO THE MOUNTAIN CABIN,

35:27.990 --> 35:29.685
GET LOADED,
AND TAKE THE BOAT OUT.

35:29.690 --> 35:31.555
PARENTS DIDN'T NEED TO KNOW.

35:31.560 --> 35:33.482
SO WE'RE GETTING HIGH
UP ON THE BALCONY.

35:33.490 --> 35:35.299
AND I HEAR A CAR PULL UP,
AND I HIDE,

35:35.300 --> 35:36.949
BUT I GOT A GOOD ANGLE.

35:36.960 --> 35:40.168
AND I SEE MY DAD AND UNCLE LEV
GET OUT OF A CAR.

35:40.170 --> 35:43.833
THEY OPEN THE TRUNK
AND PULL A COUPLE BODIES OUT.

35:43.840 --> 35:46.138
THEY ARE BLOODY AS HELL.

35:46.140 --> 35:49.530
AND SO THEY DRAG THE BODIES
INTO THE WORKSHOP.

35:49.540 --> 35:52.179
AND THE NEXT THING,
I HEAR THE POWER SAW GOING.

35:52.180 --> 35:56.048
I ALWAYS WONDERED WHY MY DAD
PUT A WOODSHOP UP IN THE CABIN.

35:56.050 --> 35:58.518
SO THE NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
HE AND UNCLE LEV

35:58.520 --> 36:01.614
ARE TAKING A COUPLE HEFTY BAGS
DOWN TO THE BOAT.

36:04.390 --> 36:08.429
MAYBE I'LL LET GORY SOROKIN
KEEP HIS SECRETS.

36:11.600 --> 36:14.728
HEY, NISH.
I'VE GOT A PRESENT FOR YOU.

36:14.740 --> 36:15.991
YOU'RE TRANSFERRING?

36:16.000 --> 36:17.399
A LIST.

36:17.400 --> 36:19.834
THE NAMES OF EVERY MEMBER
OF THE CASTLE.

36:19.840 --> 36:21.205
ALL MEN.

36:21.210 --> 36:25.749
YOU THINK THIS WILL HELP
WITH THAT LAWSUIT?

36:25.750 --> 36:27.399
OH, MY GOD.

36:28.420 --> 36:31.389
POLITICIANS.
TYCOONS. CELEBRITIES.

36:31.390 --> 36:33.449
THIS IS GOLD.

36:33.450 --> 36:37.454
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE SOME
VERY POWERFUL MEN VERY UNHAPPY.

36:37.460 --> 36:40.486
WON'T BE
THE FIRST TIME.

36:45.700 --> 36:47.759
HEY.
YOU NEED TO WALK AWAY.

36:47.770 --> 36:50.330
JUST...
I NEED TO APOLOGIZE.

36:50.340 --> 36:51.932
GREAT.
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

36:51.940 --> 36:53.202
NOW GO.

36:53.210 --> 36:54.632
I'M MEETING PIZ,
WHO, BY THE WAY,

36:54.640 --> 36:56.779
IS THE ONE YOU SHOULD BE
APOLOGIZING TO.

36:59.250 --> 37:00.842
I AM SORRY, VERONICA.

37:00.850 --> 37:01.874
I THOUGHT --

37:01.880 --> 37:03.108
WELL, YOU KNOW
WHAT I THOUGHT.

37:03.120 --> 37:05.918
I WAS HOPING
I'D SEE YOU.

37:05.920 --> 37:08.218
I DIDN'T WANT TO CARRY
THAT AROUND FOREVER.

37:08.220 --> 37:10.814
YOU LEFT IT BEHIND
IN MY ROOM.

37:13.090 --> 37:14.421
YOU KNOW WHAT?

37:14.430 --> 37:15.988
I'M GLAD WE CAUGHT YOU
ON HIDDEN CAMERA.

37:16.000 --> 37:18.560
AND I'M GLAD IT'S SUCH
A POPULAR E-MAIL ATTACHMENT,

37:18.570 --> 37:20.697
BECAUSE YOU'RE A REAL BITCH.

37:21.740 --> 37:24.664
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU SHOULD DO
WITH YOUR SUDDEN POPULARITY?

37:24.670 --> 37:27.867
JUST LAY BACK
AND ENJOY IT.

37:35.920 --> 37:38.480
LOGAN, DON'T.

37:38.490 --> 37:39.548
HE'S CONNECTED.

37:39.550 --> 37:41.017
CONNECTED CONNECTED.

37:41.020 --> 37:42.885
OH.

37:42.890 --> 37:43.959
YEAH, I WAS WONDERING.

37:43.960 --> 37:45.279
DIDN'T SEEM LIKE YOU
TO SHRUG IT OFF.

37:45.290 --> 37:48.020
HEY, SO LISTEN.
AGAIN...

37:48.030 --> 37:49.793
I APOLOGIZE.

37:49.800 --> 37:51.768
I CAN BE
PRETTY DUMB SOMETIMES.

37:51.770 --> 37:55.467
IT'S A NICE GESTURE, BUT IT'S
GONNA TAKE SOME TIME THIS TIME.

38:01.070 --> 38:03.675
[ THUD, WOMAN SCREAMS ]

38:20.860 --> 38:23.499
WANT TO HEAR
YOUR FRIEND APOLOGIZE?

38:24.400 --> 38:27.597
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN HIS APOLOGY.

38:27.600 --> 38:29.898
BUT I WOULD LIKE
MY PEN BACK.

38:33.310 --> 38:35.130
WHOEVER YOU ARE,
YOU'RE GONNA DIE.

38:35.140 --> 38:38.007
YEAH, SOMEDAY.

38:39.780 --> 38:42.908
AH, PIZ.
JUST WHO I WAS LOOKING FOR.

38:43.980 --> 38:48.917
LISTEN, MAN.
I AM TRULY SORRY FOR EVERYTHING.

39:00.700 --> 39:03.237
SO ARE YOU LIKE
THE BUTLER NOW OR...

39:03.240 --> 39:04.662
I'M JUST SAYING.

39:04.670 --> 39:06.763
ANSWERING THE DOOR KIND OF
SMELLS OF BEING DEMOTED.

39:06.770 --> 39:09.375
I LIKE TO DEAL WITH
THE MISCREANTS PERSONALLY.

39:09.380 --> 39:11.940
YES, YOU DO.
LOOK WHO DROPPED BY.

39:16.820 --> 39:17.946
VERONICA.

39:19.250 --> 39:21.047
WOULD YOU CARE
FOR SOMETHING?

39:21.050 --> 39:23.484
LEMONADE, MINERAL WATER?

39:23.490 --> 39:26.050
I CAME BY
TO BRING THIS BACK.

39:28.430 --> 39:31.467
WOULD YOU WAIT RIGHT THERE?

39:31.470 --> 39:33.563
I'M GONNA CALL
THE SHERIFF MYSELF,

39:33.570 --> 39:34.867
HAVE HIM COME ARREST YOU.

39:34.870 --> 39:37.259
GO AHEAD.
I'LL WAIT.

39:37.270 --> 39:38.601
BUT THE MOMENT THAT HAPPENS,

39:38.610 --> 39:40.362
EVERYTHING ON THIS DRIVE
GOES PUBLIC.

39:40.370 --> 39:41.974
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:42.740 --> 39:45.846
THERE'S NO WAY YOU CAN KNOW
WHAT'S ON THAT DRIVE.

39:45.850 --> 39:47.875
NOT IN A DAY.

39:50.280 --> 39:52.748
GABE HUNTLEY.
CLASS OF '74.

39:52.750 --> 39:55.389
RAN OVER SOMEONE ONE NIGHT
IN TIJUANA.

39:55.390 --> 39:58.052
GERALD CUMMINGS.
ELECTION FRAUD.

39:58.060 --> 39:59.527
THEN THERE'S THAT

39:59.530 --> 40:04.490
STEAMY BOARDING-SCHOOL INCIDENT
OF YOURS.

40:05.770 --> 40:07.897
AND WE LEAVE MY DAD
OUT OF IT.

40:11.270 --> 40:14.501
I'M AFRAID IT'S A LITTLE
TOO LATE FOR THAT, VERONICA.

40:16.110 --> 40:18.670
CLARENCE WILL
SEE YOU OUT.

40:18.680 --> 40:20.147
[ DOOR OPENS ]

40:21.280 --> 40:22.816
GOOD.
YOU'RE HOME.

40:30.490 --> 40:31.980
PREPARE FOR GUMBO.

40:31.990 --> 40:36.120
HOW DO I FIND THE TIME
TO MAKE GUMBO, YOU ASK?

40:36.130 --> 40:37.825
I MAKE TIME.

40:43.800 --> 40:47.509
YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU, RIGHT?
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

40:47.510 --> 40:49.637
OF COURSE, HONEY.

40:51.240 --> 40:53.071
I NEVER DOUBTED.

40:56.020 --> 40:58.170
EAT.

40:58.180 --> 40:59.989
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

41:01.350 --> 41:02.556
DAD?

41:03.890 --> 41:08.179
[ ALBERT HAMMOND'S
"IT NEVER RAINS IN
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA" PLAYS ]

41:14.940 --> 41:21.630
* GOT ON BOARD
A WESTBOUND 747 *

41:23.410 --> 41:30.976
* DIDN'T THINK BEFORE DECIDING
WHAT TO DO *

41:30.980 --> 41:36.953
* ALL THAT TALK
OF OPPORTUNITIES *

41:36.960 --> 41:40.657
* TV BREAKS AND MOVIES *

41:40.660 --> 41:44.323
* RANG TRUE *

41:44.330 --> 41:48.027
* SURE RANG TRUE *

41:48.030 --> 41:56.574
* SEEMS IT NEVER RAINS
IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA *

41:56.580 --> 42:04.476
* SEEMS I'VE OFTEN HEARD
THAT KIND OF TALK BEFORE *

42:04.480 --> 42:09.952
* IT NEVER RAINS
IN CALIFORNIA *
